text: Thomas Kent Wetherell (December 22, 1945 â€“ December 16, 2018) was an American politician and educator. He was born in Daytona Beach, Florida. He was a Democrat. Wetherell was the 86th Speaker of the Florida House of Representatives from 1991 to 1992. He was the 13th President of Florida State University from 2003 to 2010. Wetherell died from complications of prostate cancer on December 16, 2018 in Tallahassee, Florida, aged 72. ==References== ==Other websites== *FSU: Office of the President Category:1945 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from prostate cancer Category:Cancer deaths in Florida Category:Educators from Florida Category:Politicians from Florida Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:People from Daytona Beach, Florida Category:Members of the Florida Legislature
